Definition.WordDefinition: three-dimensional adj 1: involving or relating to three dimensions or aspects; giving the illusion of depth; "lifelike three-dimensional characters"; "a three-dimensional account of conditions under the new government"; "they shot the movie in three-D" [syn: {third-dimensional}, {three-d}] 2: having three dimensions [syn: {cubic}] [ant: {linear}, {planar}]
